  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of a bad speed sensor?",
  "response": "Here are common symptoms of a bad speed sensor:\n\n1. Check Engine Light\n- Illuminates on dashboard\n- Indicates potential sensor malfunction\n\n2. Transmission Problems\n- Erratic shifting\n- Delayed or hard shifting\n- Inability to shift gears\n- Transmission staying in neutral\n\n3. Speedometer Issues\n- Speedometer not working\n- Speedometer fluctuating or displaying incorrect speed\n- Speedometer needle moving erratically\n\n4. Cruise Control Malfunction\n- Unable to maintain constant speed\n- Cruise control not engaging\n- Sudden speed changes\n\n5. Reduced Fuel Efficiency\n- Incorrect fuel management due to inaccurate speed readings\n- Higher fuel consumption\n\n6. ABS System Problems\n- ABS warning light on\n- Reduced brake performance\n- Unstable braking\n\n7. Traction Control Complications\n- Traction control system not functioning properly\n- Unexpected wheel spin\n\n8. Engine Performance Issues\n- Loss of power\n- Rough idling\n- Stalling\n\n9. Difficulty Starting Vehicle\n- In some cases, a bad speed sensor can prevent the car from starting\n\nIf you experience multiple symptoms, have the speed sensor professionally diagnosed and replaced if necessary.",
